  "title": "ISic001489. Dedication to Hermes",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"Φάλακρος\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">Φάλακρος</span> http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/alists/listglyph.xml#triple-colon <span data-text=\"Θευδώρου\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">Θευδώρου</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"Ἑρμᾶι\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"\">Ἑρμᾶι</span> http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/alists/listglyph.xml#triple-colon <span data-text=\"ἀνέθηκε\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">ἀνέθηκε</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"Φάλακρος\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"\">ΦΑΛΑΚΡΟΣ</span>(triple-colon)<span data-text=\"Θευδώρου\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"\">ΘΕΥΔΩΡΟΥ</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"Ἑρμᾶι\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"\">ΕΡΜΑΙ</span>(triple-colon)<span data-text=\"ἀνέθηκε\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"\">ΑΝΕΘΗΚΕ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001489_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Agrigento Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic001489_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001489.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Agrigento Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic001489-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001489_rightthreequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Agrigento Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic001489_rightthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001489_rightthreequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Agrigento Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic001489_rightthreequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic001489_leftthreequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Agrigento Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic001489_leftthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001489_leftthreequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Agrigento Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo\" src=\"ISic001489_leftthreequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text based on autopsy</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>Phalakros son of Theudoros dedicated (this statue) to Hermes</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>Phalacros, figlio di Theudoros, ad Hermes dedicò</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 04.0035 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a>  </li><li> Gabrici NSA 1925 421 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392</a>  </li><li> Langlotz 1943 abb.3 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001891\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001891</a>  </li><li> De Waele 1971 32-33 no.3 pl.4 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002040\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002040</a>  </li><li> Griffo 1987 188 fig.163 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001934\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001934</a>  </li><li> Dubois 1989 <a href=\"http://www.persee.fr/doc/efr_0000-0000_1989_cat_119_1\" target=\"_blank\">183</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Letters of the early Hellenistic or late classical period. Phi has an elliptical eye; alpha has straight bar; omicron is almost full size; sigma has widely diverging top and bottom strokes; theta is smaller than other letters, with a dot in the middle; omega is open; mu has diverging first and last strokes, and the mid-point only descends half-way; epsilon has short middle stroke. Words are separated on both lines by a three vertical points.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Η-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Η type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Θ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Θ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Θ-type1.4.html\" target=\"_blank\">Θ type1.4</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Λ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Λ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type1.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type1.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Φ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Φ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Φ-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Φ type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type2.1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type2.1.1</a> </p> Line 1  18-25  Line 2  18-24  Interlineation line 1 to 2  18-20  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
